
== Purpose ==
Wiki websites are excellent resources for sharing and updating information.  This is particularly relevant for the open-source software community.  The software is easy to install and the graphical user interface is even easier for users to contribute.  

== Installation & Configuration ==
Since this wiki is hosted on AWS, I will break the installation and configuration into AWS and WikiMedia.
=== AWS ===
# Create IAM Users/Permissions
## Create Group named Ziyotek3
## Create Users and add to Ziyotek3
## Attach policies to Ziyotek3
### AmazonVPCFullAccess
### AmazonEC2ContainerServicesFullAccess
# Launch and configure VPC 
## subnet, internet gateway, route table
# Launch and configure EC2 Instance 
## Elastic IP- for wiki users to use one IP Address
## Create key pair, private key to access command line

=== WikiMedia ===
==== Installation ====
# Install epel-release 7 (not in portal)
#: yum install -y https://dl.fedoraproject.org/pub/epel/epel-release-latest-7.noarch.rpm
# Install Apache, MariaDB, PHP
#''' Install LAMP for Amazon Linux 2'''
#: amazon-linux-extras install -y lamp-mariadb10.2-php7.2 php7.2
# systemctl start/enable httpd mariadb
# Install mysql on command line, configure on graphical website
==== Configuration ====
# Create New Page
## <Wiki IP Address>/index.php/<PAGE_NAME> - simply enter desired page name after index.php to create page
#''' Enable Image Uploads '''
## yum install -y ImageMagick
## cd /var/www/html
##: chown apache:apache images/
## vi LocalSettings.php
  $wgEnableUploads = true; #LINE 72
  $wgUseImageMagick = true;
  $wgImageMagickConvertCommand = "/usr/bin/convert";
  $wgAllowCopyUploads = true;  
  $wgHashedUploadDirectory = true;
  $wgFileExtensions = array('png','gif','jpg','jpeg','doc','xls','mpp','pdf','ppt','tiff','bmp','docx', 'xlsx', 'pptx','ps','odt','ods','odp','odg');

